For Creating Api
1) command===>express --view = ejs appname
2) Create Models of Mongo DB (look models folder) and also make connection of mongo dp in app.js
3) create Api folder in routes then creates routes for each db models (routes-->api)
(look Api Folder)

For Creating Client End and utilizing api
1) views folder contain index and error ejs files ejs are use for creating layouts
2)index.ejs is the default page which will render at '/'
3)ejs file will be render by route (see index.js in routes)
4) partials will contain the master layout which will render on every page
5) site will contain the layouts of pages(views-->site)




